quran[25]{c,v,t}:
  25,53,"It is He Who has let free the two bodies of flowing water, one palatable and sweet, the other salty and bitter. Yet He has made a barrier between them, a partition that is forbidden to be passed"
  25,54,"It is He Who has created human beings from water. Then He established relationships of lineage and marriage, for your Lord has power over all things"
  25,55,"Yet they worship besides God things that can neither profit them nor harm them, and the disbeliever is a helper against his own Guardian Evolver"
  25,56,But We only sent you to give good news and advice
  25,57,"Say, “No reward do I ask of you for it but this, that each one who wills, take a straight path to his Lord.”"
  25,58,"And put your trust in Him Who lives and dies not, so praise Him, and enough is He to be acquainted with the faults of His servants"
  25,59,"He Who created the heavens and the earth, and all that is between, in six days, and is firmly established on the throne of authority, God the Merciful Benefactor. Then ask about Him, any who are acquainted with those things"
  25,60,"When it is said to them, “Prostrate to the Merciful Benefactor”, they say, “And what is the Merciful Benefactor? And why should we prostrate to that which you advise us?” It increases their flight from the truth"
  25,61,"Blessed is He Who made the constellations in the skies, and placed therein a lamp and a moon casting light"
  25,62,"And it is He Who made the night and the day to follow each other, for those who have the will to praise Him and to show their gratitude"
  25,63,"And the servants of God, the Merciful Benefactor, are those who walk on the earth with humility, and when the ignorant address them they say, “Peace.”"
  25,64,"Those who spend the night in adoration of their Lord, prostrating and standing"
  25,65,"Those who say, “Our Lord, avert from us the punishment of hell, for its punishment is indeed a terrible affliction"
  25,66,“Terrible indeed is it as a home and as a place to stay.”
  25,67,"Those who when they give, are neither irresponsible nor miserly, but are balanced between those extremes"
  25,68,"Those who do not invoke with God any other god, nor slay the soul that God has made sacred, except for just cause, and who do not engage in impermissible sex. But any who does this, not only meets punishment"
  25,69,"But the penalty on the Day of Accountability will be doubled for him, and he will dwell therein in disgrace"
  25,70,"Unless he repents, believes, and does good, for God will change the wrong of such people into good, and God is Oft-Forgiving, Mercifully Redeeming"
  25,71,"And whoever repents and does right, has truly turned to God with an acceptable conversion"
  25,72,"And those who do not support falsehood. And if they pass by futility, they pass by it with honorable avoidance"
  25,73,"Those who, when they are advised with the signs of their Lord, do not fail to register them, as if they were deaf or blind"
  25,74,"And those who pray, “Our Lord, grant to us spouses and offspring, who will be the comfort of our eyes, and make us leaders of the righteous.”"
  25,75,"Those are the ones who will be rewarded with the highest place in heaven, because of their determination. There they will be met with greetings and peace"
  25,76,"Dwelling therein, and how beautiful a home and place of rest"
  25,77,"Say to the rejecters, “My Lord is not upset by you, if you do not call on Him, but you have indeed rejected Him, so soon will come the inevitable punishment.”"